|DA^\prime|
|DA^\prime| = |CA^\prime| + |DC| = |AC|\cos C + |DC| = k \sin B \cos C + |DC|
\frac{|DC|}{|CB^\prime|} = \frac{\sin \angle DB^\prime C}{\sin \angle B^\prime DC} \implies |DC| = |BC| \cos C \cdot \frac{\sin \angle DB^\prime C}{\sin \angle B^\prime DC} = k \sin A \cos C \cdot \frac{\sin \angle DB^\prime C}{\sin \angle B^\prime DC}
